dev.marksman.kraftwerk

Class Cogenerator<A>

  • java.lang.Object
    • dev.marksman.kraftwerk.Cogenerator<A>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - the input type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functor.Contravariant<A,Cogenerator<?>>

    public abstract class Cogenerator<A>
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functor.Contravariant<A,Cogenerator<?>>
    A strategy for applying a value to a Seed to create a new Seed. The dual to a Generator.

    Cogenerators are used to build Generators of functions. A Cogenerator is required for each formal parameter of the function.

    Cogenerators must be pure, referentially transparent, and total. In other words, they must return a Seed for any input Seed and any value of type A, and it must return the same output Seed for subsequent calls with the same inputs.
